        },
        {
          "key": "D",
          "text": "c\u00b2"
        }
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "B",
      "explanation": "E[c] = c for any constant c. A constant always takes its own value with probability 1.",
      "difficulty": "easy"
    },
    {
      "id": "mcq-13",
      "question": "If X and Y are independent, then E[XY] equals:",
      "options": [
        {
